Halve @potato buns{2} and toast in a #toaster{} or #9.5-10-inch stainless steel pan{} until golden. Place @pulled pork{8%oz}(standard meat) in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}; using two #forks{}, shred into smaller pieces.

To bowl with pork, add @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp}, half the @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}, half the @bold & savory steak spice{1/2%tbsp}, 1 tsp @white wine vinegar{1%tsp}, 1 tsp water, and a pinch of @pepper{pinch}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{2%minutes}. Set aside until ready to use.

> For 4 servings, use all the paprika, all the Steak Spice, 2 tsp vinegar, and 2 tsp water.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%oz}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @white wine vinegar{1%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 tsp vinegar and 1/2 tsp sugar.

Add @gouda cheese{2%slices} to bottom buns and top with as much pork as you like.

Top with @sliced dill pickle{1} and as much slaw as you like. Close buns and divide sandos between plates. Serve with any remaining slaw, pickle, and pork on the side.

> Pulled Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.